p: Feed intake (FI), body weight (BW), and body weight gain (BWG) as the FI-to-BWG ratio were measured according to the methods reported by Alagawany et al. [ 16]. At week 13, five rabbits/group were weighed and killed to evaluate the carcass characteristics. All carcass parameters (the main body, liver, head, kidneys, lungs, heart, and other total edible parts) and dressing percentage were measured [ 17].
